Package model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ItemsComposite.AddStrategy
    This class represents the interface for the move strategies.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Assignment
    This class represents the Assignments pieces that must be obtained by the player to end the game.
    Coin
    This class represents the Coin pieces that can be collected by the player to gain points.
    Door
    This class represents the Doors in the game.
    Empty
    This class is used by the View package for displaying empty tiles.
    Game
    This class represents the game board.
    Item
    This class represents the abstract notion of an Item.
    ItemsComposite
    This class represents the Composite Item pieces that can contain a collection of Item objects - Following the Composite Pattern, this class is a representation of a Composite object.
    Key
    This class represents a Key object that are used to traverse through doors.
    Location
    This class is used to store the x and y location of a Piece.
    ModelMain
    This class is used to test the functionality of the model without running application.
    MovableStrategy
    This class implements MovableStrategy.
    NonMovableStrategy
    This class implements Non-Movable Strategy.
    Parser
    This class is used to parse the game from the file.
    Piece
    This class represents the abstract notation of a Piece that is placed in the Game
    Player
    This class represents the Player in the Game.
    Position
    This class is used to store Room and the Location a Piece in the game.
    Room
    This class represents the Room board.
    Wall
    This class represents the Walls in the game.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Direction
    This class represents the Direction that represents the direction of a piece in the game.
